  "text": "The difficulty in anaesthetizing GPs is due to a combination of factors. The choice of anaesthetics is limited, as a venous induction in the awake state is not viable or the anaesthetic does not provide for a quick recovery to enable fast body temperature and energy regulation. Also the evaluation of anaesthetic depth requires experience, anaesthesia and species specific knowledge, as reflex responses and reactions to anaesthetics vary between anaesthetic agent, individual and intra-individually, especially with KX [CITATION_1] . Therefore GPs profit from a quickly reversible anaesthetic, close monitoring during and after anaesthesia and a qualified and experienced anaesthetist.",
